## KNOWN-ERROR REGISTER
# (unchanged from v7; plus 4 new D11-specific entries below)
#
# 10. `InvalidIdentityToken: Token has invalid audience` (AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity)
#     Cause: Audience in the OIDC JWT ≠ `:aud` in trust policy condition.
#     Fix:   GitHub: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v4 sets aud=sts.amazonaws.com
#            automatically — DON'T override with `audience:` input unless you also
#            update the trust policy. GitLab: id_tokens.<name>.aud MUST be 'sts.amazonaws.com'.
#
# 11. `Lambda function ... already exists` (sam deploy after manual create)
#     Cause: Migration gate skipped — manual Lambdas collide with SAM-named ones.
#     Fix:   bash scripts/preflight-lambda-cap.sh <learner> --delete-manual; then sam deploy.
#
# 12. `EnvironmentVariableUpdated` change set fails (sam deploy)
#     Cause: SAM tries to update env vars on a Lambda whose alias is mid-deploy.
#     Fix:   Wait for the current CodeDeploy deployment to complete; or sam deploy --no-fail-on-empty-changeset.
#
# 13. `CREATE_FAILED: ... already exists` on AWS::Logs::LogGroup
#     Cause: Lambda runtime auto-created the log group before CFN got to it.
#     Fix:   Pre-create log groups explicitly OR delete the auto-created group before sam deploy.
#            Permanent fix: use the LogGroup + DependsOn + LoggingConfig.LogGroup pattern.

