## DEPLOY CONTEXT
# Use this block when Cascade scaffolds ANY infra/*.yaml, .gitlab-ci.yml,
# IAM trust policy, or anything else deploy-adjacent. Applies from Day 11.

- SAM CLI version: 1.115+ required (older versions miss DeploymentPreference fields)
- Stack naming contract:
    foundation:  accelya-foundation-<learner>                    (stateful, retained)
    app:         accelya-app-<learner>                           (manual deploy from trainer's account)
    app per MR:  accelya-app-<branch-slug>                       (CI deploys these; auto-cleaned on MR close)
- Two-stack split (MANDATORY):
    foundation contains: DDB tables, Kinesis streams, SQS queues, SNS topics
                         (anything carrying state, subscribers, or stable ARNs)
    app contains:        Lambdas, Step Functions, dashboards, alarms, IAM roles
                         (anything that should redeploy per MR)
    app references foundation via !ImportValue accelya-foundation-<learner>-<OutputName>
    NEVER duplicate stateful resources in the app stack.

- DeletionPolicy MANDATORY on EVERY stateful resource in foundation:
    DeletionPolicy: Retain
    UpdateReplacePolicy: Retain
    Pair MUST appear together — Cascade auto-fails the review on either missing.

- Every Lambda in app stack MUST have:
    AutoPublishAlias: live
    DeploymentPreference:
      Type: Linear10PercentEvery1Minute
      Hooks:
        PreTraffic: !GetAtt PreTrafficHook.Arn
      Alarms:
        - !Ref IteratorAgeAlarm
        - !Ref BedrockThrottleAlarm
    (The pretraffic-hook Lambda itself is the only exception — it would be self-referential.)

- Every Lambda MUST have explicit AWS::Logs::LogGroup:
    AWS::Logs::LogGroup with:
      LogGroupName: !Sub /aws/lambda/<fn-name>
      RetentionInDays: 14
      DeletionPolicy: Retain
      UpdateReplacePolicy: Retain
    Lambda block with:
      DependsOn: <FnName>LogGroup            # CFN must create LogGroup BEFORE Function
      LoggingConfig:
        LogGroup: !Ref <FnName>LogGroup       # binds Function to OUR log group
    Without this, Lambda runtime auto-creates the LogGroup with Never Expire,
    and CFN fails on next deploy with 'already exists'.

- OIDC trust policy contract (GitHub primary):
    Principal.Federated: arn:aws:iam::<account>:oidc-provider/token.actions.githubusercontent.com
    Action: sts:AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity
    Condition:
      StringEquals:
        token.actions.githubusercontent.com:aud: sts.amazonaws.com   # default of configure-aws-credentials@v4
      StringEquals (protected main):
        token.actions.githubusercontent.com:sub: repo:<owner>/<repo>:ref:refs/heads/main
      StringLike (feature branches):
        token.actions.githubusercontent.com:sub: repo:<owner>/<repo>:ref:refs/heads/module-11-*
      StringLike (PR builds):
        token.actions.githubusercontent.com:sub: repo:<owner>/<repo>:pull_request
    NEVER use: sub: '*' OR sub: 'repo:*' OR aud: '*'.

- OIDC trust policy contract (GitLab appendix-only):
    Principal.Federated: arn:aws:iam::<account>:oidc-provider/gitlab.com
    Condition.StringEquals: gitlab.com:aud=sts.amazonaws.com
    Condition.StringLike: gitlab.com:sub=project_path:<group>/<project>:ref_type:branch:ref:module-11-*
    NEVER use: sub: '*' OR sub: 'project_path:*'.

- Pre-deploy guard (CI):
    scripts/preflight-lambda-cap.sh runs BEFORE sam deploy.
    Counts list-functions + list-stacks; fails CI early with human message
    if app-stack creation would breach the programme cap of 12 (= 11 + 1 buffer).

- 4 scanners block merge:
    bandit (Python SAST) — src/**/*.py
    semgrep (multi-language) — src/ + tests/
    cfn-lint (CloudFormation schema) — infra/template-*.yaml
    cfn-nag (CFN security patterns) — infra/
    Suppressions per-finding in committed YAML with rule ID + reason.
    NEVER use tflint — it's Terraform-only, wrong tool for SAM/CFN.

- HITL dim 9 (NEW today) — Deploy Auditability, max 15, pass ≥ 10:
    1. DeletionPolicy on stateful (foundation)
    2. OIDC scope narrow (no wildcard sub)
    3. IAM minimum (no wildcard Resource on write/modify verbs)
    4. Rollback wired (AutoPublishAlias + DeploymentPreference + Alarms)
    5. Migration gate evidence (snapshot + delete + verify count=0)
    Each scored 0-3.

- 5 auto-fail red flags (Cascade PR-review BLOCKS regardless of total):
    1. Static AWS key in CI secrets/variables:
         GitHub: gh secret list && gh variable list
                 grep -iE '^aws_(access_key_id|secret_access_key|session_token)$'
         GitLab: glab variable list | grep -iE '^aws_...'
       returns ANY result → BLOCK.
       (Reference to ${{ secrets.AWS_OIDC_ROLE_ARN }} is OK — that's just a role ARN.)
    2. OIDC sub wildcard:
         grep -E '"(token\.actions\.githubusercontent\.com|gitlab\.com):sub":\s*"\*"|"sub":\s*"repo:\*"|project_path:\*' infra/oidc-trust-policy.json
       returns ANY result → BLOCK.
    3. Wildcard Resource on write IAM verb:
         cfn-nag rule W11 fires → BLOCK.
    4. Stateful resource without DeletionPolicy: Retain:
         Any AWS::DynamoDB::Table, AWS::Kinesis::Stream, AWS::S3::Bucket,
         AWS::SNS::Topic, AWS::SQS::Queue in foundation.yaml without Retain → BLOCK.
    5. Lambda in app stack without DeploymentPreference + Alarms wired:
         Any AWS::Serverless::Function (except pretraffic-hook) missing
         AutoPublishAlias + DeploymentPreference.Alarms → BLOCK.

- Manual rollback command (memorise — single-line):
    aws lambda update-alias --function-name <fn>-<learner> \
      --name live --function-version $PREV_VERSION

- Forbidden patterns:
    - Static AWS keys in GitHub secrets / GitLab CI variables (use OIDC)
    - OIDC sub wildcards (repo:* or project_path:*)
    - Stateful resource in foundation without DeletionPolicy: Retain
    - Stateful resource defined in app stack
    - Lambda in app stack without AutoPublishAlias + DeploymentPreference + Alarms
    - sam deploy without --capabilities CAPABILITY_IAM
    - tflint in CI (wrong tool for SAM)
    - Hand-rolled CloudFormation for Lambda + alias + version (use AutoPublishAlias)
    - Mutating foundation stack from PR pipelines (only trainer runbook touches it)
    - Skipping the preflight script in CI
    - Using ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }} or similar in GitHub workflows

